%hr
#quick-ref-information
  .matrix
    %table
      %tbody
        %tr
          %td.code <code>IGNORECASE</code>
          %td Perform case-insensitive matching.
        %tr
          %td.code <code>MULTILINE</code>
          %td When specified, the pattern character '^' matches at the beginning of the string and at the beginning of each line.
        %tr
          %td.code <code>DOTALL</code>
          %td Make the '.' special character match any character at all, including a newline; without this flag, '.' will match anything except a newline.
        %tr
          %td.code <code>UNICODE</code>
          %td Make \w, \W, \b, \B, \d, \D, \s and \S dependent on the Unicode character properties database.
        %tr
          %td.code <code>VERBOSE</code>
          %td This flag allows you to write regular expressions that look nicer. Whitespace within the pattern is ignored.

